parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and complete loss of tire tread can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire tread is torn off from sidewall to sidewall
exposing the metal casing
loss of tire pressure
vibration or shaking of the vehicle
difficulty steering or maintaining control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handles can prevent occupants from exiting the vehicle in an emergency, potentially leading to serious injury or even fatalities.
symptoms: The door handle breaks
the door handle does not function
the door cannot be opened from the outside
the door cannot be opened from the inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and failure of the rear axle can cause the axle to break away from its mount, leading to loss of vehicle control, damage to the vehicle, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear axle is rusted or corroded
the rear axle is loose or detached from its mount
the vehicle is difficult to control or handle
the vehicle is pulling to one side
unusual noises or vibrations are coming from the rear of the vehicle.
